-- China May Introduce More Property Tightening Steps in Quarter, Nomura Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-04T01:02:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-04/china-may-introduce-more-property-tightening-steps-in-quarter-nomura-says.html
China may introduce more property
tightening measures in the fourth quarter this year amid signs
of a price recovery, according to Nomura Securities Co.  The likely policies are a property tax and the enforcement
of the so-called land added-value tax in the “overheated
cities,” Nomura said in a report.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Allen Wan at 
 awan3@bloomberg.net  